File: A City of Tshwane Health official looks on as she conducts a screening exercise on a taxi operator before testing for the COVID-19 at the Bloed Street Mall in Pretoria Central Business District. JOHANNESBURG - The Health Department has reported 2,585 new COVID-19 cases in South Africa. The department also reported 126 more COVID-19 related deaths, taking the death toll to 13,628. READ: COVID-19: No major spike expected under Level 2, says Karim Forty-eight patients died from KwaZulu-Natal, 33 from Gauteng, 25 from Eastern Cape and 20 from Western Cape. Recoveries in South Africa are now at 531,338, which translates to a recovery rate of 86%. Health Media Release 27 August 2020.Pages V1 by eNCA.com on Scribd   - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.